Data Preparation

Load data, compute daily booking and revenues, convert days of week e dates

data <- read_excel("C:/Users/Utente/OneDrive/Desktop/Lavoro/Business projects/Flights Revenue and Load Factor Analysis/Flight data.xlsx")

data_by_flight <- data %>%
  group_by(`Flight Number`)  %>%
  arrange(desc(`Days Until Departure`))%>%
  arrange(`Flight Number`)  %>% 
  mutate(lag_total_booked = lag(`Total Booked`) )  %>% 
  mutate (flights_booked_on_day = `Total Booked` - lag_total_booked) %>% 
  mutate(lag_total_revenue = lag(`Total Revenue`) )  %>% 
  mutate (revenue_on_day = `Total Revenue` - lag_total_revenue)



data_by_flight$Converted_Date <- as.Date(data_by_flight$`Departure Date`) - data_by_flight$`Days Until Departure`
data_by_flight$Day_of_Week <- weekdays(as.Date(data_by_flight$Converted_Date))

Daily bookings, Revenues and Fares over date

Daily Booked Seats vs date

# Create a list of unique flight numbers
flight_numbers <- unique(data$`Flight Number`)

# Generate separate plots for each flight
for (flight in flight_numbers) {
  # Filter the data for the specific flight
  flight_data <- subset(data_by_flight, `Flight Number` == flight)
  
  # Create the scatterplot
  p <- ggplot(flight_data, aes(x =Converted_Date, y= flights_booked_on_day)) +
    geom_line() +
    labs(
      title = paste("Scatterplot for Flight", flight),
      x = "Date",
      y = "Daily Booked Seats"
    ) +
    theme_minimal()+
      facet_wrap(~ `Flight Number`, scales = "free")  # Allow each facet to have independent scales

  
  # Print the plot to the plotting window
  print(p)
}

Regressions

1.The Fares’ effect on number of daily bookings

# Create a scatterplot with facets for each flight number and independent axes
ggplot(data_by_flight, aes(x = `Fare FR`, y = flights_booked_on_day)) +
  geom_point(size = 3, alpha = 0.7) +
  labs(
    title = "Scatterplot of Bookings vs Fare FR by Flight Number",
    x = "Fare (FR)",
    y = "Number of Bookings"
  ) +
  theme_minimal() +
  facet_wrap(~ `Flight Number`, scales = "free")  # Allow each facet to have independent scales
## Warning: Removed 4 rows containing missing values or values outside the scale range
## (`geom_point()`).

# Ensure Day_of_Week is a factor ordered from Monday to Sunday
data_by_flight$Day_of_Week <- factor(
  data_by_flight$Day_of_Week, 
  levels = c("Monday", "Tuesday", "Wednesday", "Thursday", "Friday", "Saturday", "Sunday")
)

# Run regression for each flight
BOOKING_model_FR101 <- lm(
  flights_booked_on_day ~ 0 + `Fare FR` + `Days Until Departure` + Day_of_Week, 
  data = data_by_flight[data_by_flight$`Flight Number` == "FR101", ]
)
BOOKING_model_FR102 <- lm(
  flights_booked_on_day ~ 0 + `Fare FR` + `Days Until Departure` + Day_of_Week, 
  data = data_by_flight[data_by_flight$`Flight Number` == "FR102", ]
)
BOOKING_model_FR103 <- lm(
  flights_booked_on_day ~ 0 + `Fare FR` + `Days Until Departure` + Day_of_Week, 
  data = data_by_flight[data_by_flight$`Flight Number` == "FR103", ]
)
BOOKING_model_FR104 <- lm(
  flights_booked_on_day ~ 0 + `Fare FR` + `Days Until Departure` + Day_of_Week, 
  data = data_by_flight[data_by_flight$`Flight Number` == "FR104", ]
)

# Generate regression tables using huxreg
BOOKING_regression_results <- huxreg(
  "Bookings FR101" = BOOKING_model_FR101, 
  "Bookings FR102" = BOOKING_model_FR102, 
  "Bookings FR103" = BOOKING_model_FR103, 
  "Bookings FR104" = BOOKING_model_FR104
)

# Print the regression tables
print(BOOKING_regression_results)

REVENUE_model_FR102 <- lm(revenue_on_day ~ 0 + `Fare FR` + `Days Until Departure` + Day_of_Week, data = data_by_flight[data_by_flight$`Flight Number` == "FR102", ])
REVENUE_model_FR103 <- lm(revenue_on_day ~ 0 + `Fare FR` + `Days Until Departure` + Day_of_Week, data = data_by_flight[data_by_flight$`Flight Number` == "FR103", ])
